The paper proposes an end-to-end automated meta-learning pipeline for approximating the optimal Q function for contextual bandits problems. This involves using machine learning techniques to optimize exploration vs exploitation schedules and evaluate performance on synthetic and open source datasets. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science). Additionally, the paper involves data analysis and optimization, which could place it in the sub-categories cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
